    "In this type of research, variables are manipulated, but participants are not randomly assigned to groups.",
    "Instead, groups can be formed based on convenience, specific characteristics of the participants, and geographic location, among other criteria.",
    "The results are then compared between the groups to determine if the intervention had any effect.",
